The existing final_report.md (written by a previous agent) is INCOMPLETE because:
1. It doesn't mention ACP at all - this is the most important finding
2. It recommends Pattern A (self-polling) which c5-internal explicitly says NOT to do
3. The ACP approach is fundamentally different: orchestrator controls the loop, LLM just responds to prompts

The correct architecture is:
- Python orchestrator manages the work queue (asyncio.Queue or filesystem)
- Python orchestrator spawns 4-10 `kiro-cli acp` processes
- Each ACP process is a persistent worker
- Orchestrator sends prompts via JSON-RPC, receives responses
- LLM never needs to "poll" - it just responds to each prompt
- This is the pattern used by Botctl, KiroClaw, and 10+ other production systems

