# Persistent kiro-cli Agents — ACP Protocol, 30s Timeout, Disabled Compaction

**Investigation:** e8430987 | **Date:** 2026-05-13

## The Answer: `kiro-cli acp`

`kiro-cli acp` starts kiro-cli as a JSON-RPC 2.0 server over stdin/stdout. One process handles unlimited prompts. MCP tools initialize once. The orchestrator controls the work loop — the LLM just responds to prompts.

```bash
kiro-cli acp --agent debate-worker --trust-all-tools
```

Protocol: `initialize → session/new → session/prompt (loop)`

Key methods: `session/new`, `session/prompt`, `session/update` (streaming), `session/load`, `session/cancel`, `session/request_permission` (auto-approve with --trust-all-tools).

Turn completion signal: `session/update` with `sessionUpdate: "turn_end"`.

## Critical Settings (verified in ~/.kiro/settings/cli.json)

- `mcp.noInteractiveTimeout: 30000` — **--no-interactive calls timeout after 30 seconds**. A debate turn with multiple tool calls will exceed this. ACP has no such limit. This makes ACP mandatory for the debate system.
- `chat.disableAutoCompaction: true` — Auto-compaction is DISABLED. ACP sessions must be reset programmatically every ~40 turns (`session/new`). Do NOT rely on auto-compaction.

## --resume-id Does NOT Restore LLM Memory

Confirmed by live test: `--resume-id` restores session metadata but does NOT inject prior conversation history into the LLM context in `--no-interactive` mode. Memory must be passed explicitly in each prompt.

## Agent Format Is JSON, Not YAML

`~/.kiro/agents/*.json` — JSON format. Fields: `name`, `description`, `prompt`, `tools`, `allowedTools`, `mcpServers`.

## Don't Make the LLM Poll

Pattern A (self-polling agent with shell while loop) is fragile:
- LLMs are trained to complete tasks and stop
- Shell loop output accumulates in context
- With compaction disabled, context fills and crashes

Use ACP instead: orchestrator controls the loop, LLM just responds to prompts.

## Elastic Scaling

- `pgrep -c kiro-cli` — system-wide process count
- System cap: 15 processes
- Pool: 4 min, 10 max
- Scale up when queue depth > active workers * 2
- Respawn dead workers (check `proc.returncode is not None`)

## Complete kiro-cli chat Flags

`--no-interactive`, `--agent`, `--trust-all-tools`, `--trust-tools`, `--resume`, `--resume-id`, `--resume-picker`, `--list-sessions`, `--delete-session`, `--model`, `--wrap`, `--require-mcp-startup`, `--tui`, `--legacy-ui`, `--agent-engine`

NO `--session`, `--persistent`, `--file`, `--context`, `--system-prompt` flags.

## Filesystem Queue Pattern

```
queue/pending/   <- orchestrator writes
queue/processing/ <- worker claims (atomic mv)
queue/done/      <- worker writes result
queue/failed/    <- failed items
```

`rename(2)` is atomic on same filesystem (POSIX). Safe for concurrent workers.
